WEBVTT

00:06.206 --> 00:09.643 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Good evening. I'm
Gwen Ifill. Judy Woodruff is on
assignment.

00:09.643 --> 00:14.181 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: Los
Angeles shuts down the nation's
second largest school district

00:14.181 --> 00:18.085 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
after an e-mail threat
targeting students.

00:18.085 --> 00:22.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Also ahead: Baltimore is on high
alert, as the jury is sent back
after declaring a deadlock

00:22.155 --> 00:25.425 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in the Freddie Gray case.

00:25.425 --> 00:29.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Plus: Terrorism and safety
concerns take center stage at
tonight's Republican
presidential

00:29.129 --> 00:31.031 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
debate.

00:31.031 --> 00:35.802 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Miles O'Brien gets a reality
check on solar and wind energy.

00:35.802 --> 00:39.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD SADOWAY, Massachusetts
Institute of Technology: The
issue is that we don't have

00:39.740 --> 00:46.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a battery technology that can
meet the rigorous performance
requirements of the grid,
namely,

00:46.513 --> 00:49.950 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
super low-cost and super
long service lifetime.

00:49.950 --> 00:52.019 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:52.019 --> 00:57.724 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:57.724 --> 01:09.903 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Public schools
across Los Angeles went dark
today, shuttered by the fear of

01:09.903 --> 01:16.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a terror strike. It came in the
form of an e-mail that warned of
mass violence.

01:16.276 --> 01:21.515 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The threat brought the Los
Angeles Unified School District,
covering 600 square miles,

01:21.515 --> 01:27.587 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to a halt. All 1,200 schools
were shut down before classes
started for the day. Many of

01:27.587 --> 01:32.359 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the 640,000 students were forced
to turn around and head home.

01:32.359 --> 01:36.530 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And Superintendent Ramon
Cortines hastily convened a news
conference.

01:36.530 --> 01:38.732 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RAMON CORTINES, Superintendent,
Los Angeles Unified School
District: I think it is
important

01:38.732 --> 01:47.774 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that I take the precaution based
on what has happened recently
and what has happened in

01:47.774 --> 01:49.843 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the past.

01:49.843 --> 01:55.716 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Cortines was
referring to the rampage two
weeks ago in nearby San
Bernardino,

01:55.716 --> 02:02.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
where a married couple, Syed
Farook and Tashfeen Malik,
killed 14 people at a holiday
party.

02:02.189 --> 02:06.660 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As L.A. police fanned out and
began checking schools today,
officials said the e-mailed

02:06.660 --> 02:11.398 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
threat came from Germany and
mentioned everything from guns
to bombs to nerve gas.

02:11.398 --> 02:14.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For many parents,
it was unnerving.

02:14.167 --> 02:20.240 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MAN: Well, if it's real,
watching from what happened in
San Bernardino, that's pretty

02:20.240 --> 02:25.779 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
close to home. And now this one
here, even closer, that's kind
of scary.

02:25.779 --> 02:29.916 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: Confusion, chaos,
nervousness. You're not certain
of what's going on, what's
entailed

02:29.916 --> 02:33.653 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
behind it. So, there's a lot of
different emotions behind that.

02:33.653 --> 02:38.158 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Meanwhile, officials
in New York City said they
received a similar, if not

02:38.158 --> 02:43.930 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the same, message. They
discounted it as a hoax,
possibly based on a television
show.

02:43.930 --> 02:47.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRATTON, New York City
Police Commissioner: The
language in the e-mail would
lead us to

02:47.267 --> 02:55.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
believe that this is not a
jihadist initiative, for
example, that Allah wasn't
spelled with

02:55.776 --> 03:00.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a capital A. That would be
incredible to think that any
jihadist wouldn't spell Allah
with

03:00.914 --> 03:03.583 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a capital A.

03:03.583 --> 03:09.322 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think the initiator, the
instigator of the threat may be
a "Homeland" fan, basically

03:09.322 --> 03:14.795 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
watching "Homeland" episodes,
that it mirrors a lot of recent
episodes on "Homeland."

03:14.795 --> 03:18.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Moreover, Mayor Bill
de Blasio argued it's vital to
keep schools open and

03:18.198 --> 03:20.067 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
not overreact.

03:20.067 --> 03:23.603 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BILL DE BLASIO (D), Mayor of New
York: It's very important to
realize there are people

03:23.603 --> 03:27.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who want us to fundamentally
change our lifestyle and our
values, and we will never give
in

03:27.107 --> 03:29.476 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to that.

03:29.476 --> 03:33.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: As the hours ticked
by, Los Angeles Mayor Eric
Garcetti pushed back at
criticism

03:33.580 --> 03:36.216 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
it was wrong to
close L.A. schools.

03:36.216 --> 03:40.454 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ERIC GARCETTI (D), Mayor of Los
Angeles: We will continue to
hope that this is nothing

03:40.454 --> 03:45.358 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and that our children can be
back at school tomorrow. But, as
a parent and as a mayor,

03:45.358 --> 03:51.231 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
certainly, I am here to support
this school district as it seeks
our help to ensure that

03:51.231 --> 03:53.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we can look at each one of these
campuses and make sure that they
are safe for all of

03:53.967 --> 03:55.702 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our children.

03:55.702 --> 03:59.239 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The search and the
investigation continued into the
evening, assisted by the

03:59.239 --> 04:00.874 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
FBI.

04:00.874 --> 04:07.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The White House said it wouldn't
second guess the decision in Los
Angeles, but a congressman

04:07.147 --> 04:12.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from the area, Adam Schiff, said
it now appears the threat was
indeed a hoax.

04:12.552 --> 04:17.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the day's other news, the
United Nations' nuclear agency
formally ended a decade-long

04:17.991 --> 04:29.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
probe into Iran's nuclear
program. But, in Vienna, the
head of the International Atomic
Energy Agency

04:29.703 --> 04:33.773 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
said there's no sign the
work has continued.

04:33.773 --> 04:36.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YUKIYA AMANO, Director General,
International Atomic Energy
Agency: The agency has no
credible

04:36.743 --> 04:44.284 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
indications of activities in
Iran relevant to the development
of nuclear explosive devices

04:44.284 --> 04:55.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
after 2009, nor has the agency
found any credible indications
of the diversion of nuclear
material

04:55.228 --> 05:00.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in connection with the possible
military dimensions to Iran's
nuclear program.

05:00.700 --> 05:05.872 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The end of the
investigation clears the way for
implementing a July deal that

05:05.872 --> 05:10.443 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the U.S. and other powers
reached with Iran. It calls for
curbing the nuclear program in

05:10.443 --> 05:14.714 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
exchange for relief from
economic sanctions.

05:14.714 --> 05:19.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Human rights activists in
Nigeria are accusing the
country's military of carrying
out a massacre

05:19.653 --> 05:25.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of hundreds of Shiite Muslims.
They say it happened over the
weekend in the city of Zaria.

05:25.091 --> 05:29.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The army says the Shiites
attacked a military convoy.
Protests over the incident broke
out

05:29.930 --> 05:33.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
today in another city. A Shiite
spokesman says police fired on
the crowd and killed

05:33.533 --> 05:36.870 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at least three people.

05:36.870 --> 05:41.608 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Defense Secretary Ash Carter
called for the rest of the world
today to ramp up military

05:41.608 --> 05:46.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
efforts against the Islamic
State group. Carter spoke to
U.S. and other troops stationed
in

05:46.780 --> 05:50.550 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Southern Turkey. They're taking
part in the air campaign against
ISIS targets in Iraq

05:50.550 --> 05:52.819 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and Syria.

05:52.819 --> 05:56.289 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ASHTON CARTER, U.S. Defense
Secretary: We really are looking
for the rest of the world

05:56.289 --> 06:03.897 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to step up. America is stepping
up. We need our allies and
partners around the world to

06:03.897 --> 06:09.603 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
step up and do more. And that's
true in Europe. It's true in the
Gulf. It's true -- by Europe,

06:09.603 --> 06:13.840 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I mean, all of NATO,
including Turkey.

06:13.840 --> 06:18.912 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Carter also called
for Turkey to seal off the rest
of its border against

06:18.912 --> 06:25.619 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ISIS smuggling. And Turkey today
joined a new 34-nation Islamic
military alliance battling

06:25.619 --> 06:30.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
terrorism. It's led by Saudi
Arabia, but doesn't include
Iran, Iraq or Syria.

06:30.991 --> 06:35.929 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Yemen, a week-long cease-fire
took effect today between Shiite
rebels and government

06:35.929 --> 06:42.402 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
forces backed by the Saudis and
other Arab states. Even so,
security officials said shelling

06:42.402 --> 06:47.474 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and ground clashes continued in
places. The truce was timed to
coincide with U.N.-brokered

06:47.474 --> 06:52.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
peace talks in Geneva. A special
U.N. envoy urged both sides to
end the war.

06:52.812 --> 06:56.116 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ISMAIL OULD CHEIKH AHMED, U.N.
Special Envoy for Yemen (through
translator): Today, you

06:56.116 --> 07:00.553 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are the decision makers, and
before you lies a historic
responsibility. Are you going to

07:00.553 --> 07:04.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
abandon Yemen and its people and
lead the country into further
violence and slaughter?

07:04.591 --> 07:09.129 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Or are you going to put Yemen
first and ensure the people of
Yemen can live the dignified

07:09.129 --> 07:11.898 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
life they deserve? You are
writing the history of modern
Yemen, and you alone have the
power

07:11.898 --> 07:14.701 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to overturn the situation.

07:14.701 --> 07:18.772 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The World Health
Organization says the warring
factions have promised to

07:18.772 --> 07:24.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
allow unconditional movement of
supplies and medical teams
during the cease-fire.

07:24.778 --> 07:29.549 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Secretary of State John Kerry
reports progress on plans for
Syrian peace talks this week.

07:29.549 --> 07:33.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kerry met with Russian President
Vladimir Putin in Moscow today
and said they found

07:33.887 --> 07:38.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
common ground on which Syrian
opposition groups to include in
the talks. Russia backs the

07:38.591 --> 07:43.129 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Syrian government, while the
U.S. supports moderate rebels.

07:43.129 --> 07:47.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Back in this country,
congressional negotiators worked
to finish sweeping tax and
spending

07:47.600 --> 07:52.539 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bills to fund the government for
the rest of the fiscal year. If
they agree, the trillion-dollar

07:52.539 --> 07:58.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
package would also lift a
40-year-old ban on U.S. oil
exports, as Republicans want.

07:58.778 --> 08:01.715 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it would renew tax credits
for producers of renewable
energy, something Democrats have

08:01.715 --> 08:04.784 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
asked for.

08:04.784 --> 08:09.656 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Republican governor of Texas
has ordered National Guard
troops to remain at the state's

08:09.656 --> 08:14.194 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
border with Mexico. Their
mission was supposed to end this
month, but Governor Greg Abbott

08:14.194 --> 08:19.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
says more than 10,000 children
crossed into the U.S. in October
and November without parents.

08:19.966 --> 08:23.570 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's double the
number from a year ago.

08:23.570 --> 08:28.141 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Wall Street gained ground
for a second day. The Dow Jones
industrial average was

08:28.141 --> 08:37.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
up 156 points to close near
17525. The Nasdaq rose 43
points, and the S&amp;P 500 added
21.

08:37.951 --> 08:43.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
a new focus on terrorism as the
GOP debates; Baltimore's

08:43.790 --> 08:48.661 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Freddie Gray case in the hands
of the jury; a congressional
crackdown on financial advisers;

08:48.661 --> 09:01.875 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and much more.

09:01.875 --> 09:05.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tonight marks the fifth time
Republican candidates will face
off on the debate stage, but it

09:05.879 --> 09:09.416 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
will be the first time they have
met since the attacks in Paris
and San Bernardino.

09:09.416 --> 09:12.786 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Political director Lisa
Desjardins reports.

09:12.786 --> 09:17.157 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: National
security, it's now the dominant
theme for 2016 in speech after

09:17.157 --> 09:18.691 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
speech.

09:18.691 --> 09:21.261 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate: We don't feel safe
anymore.

09:21.261 --> 09:23.696 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: From one
news conference to the next.

09:23.696 --> 09:25.398 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SEN. TED CRUZ (R-TX),
Presidential Candidate: We are,
today, in a time of war.

09:25.398 --> 09:28.601 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Again and
again in TV appearances.

09:28.601 --> 09:29.269 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SEN. MARCO RUBIO (R-FL),
Presidential Candidate: They're
afraid of what they're reading
in

09:29.269 --> 09:30.904 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the press.

09:30.904 --> 09:35.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The attacks on
Paris and San Bernardino have
fueled the new urgency.

09:35.074 --> 09:41.114 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A new NBC News/Wall Street
Journal poll lists national
security as the clear number one

09:41.114 --> 09:47.587 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
priority of all voters; 40
percent chose it. But the number
was even greater for Republican

09:47.587 --> 09:53.026 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
voters; 58 percent said fighting
terror should be government's
top priority.

09:53.026 --> 09:58.832 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The candidates have been quick
to react, and a campaign that
was focused on outsiders is

09:58.832 --> 10:03.036 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
now highlighting the experience
of some establishment
candidates, putting those with
less foreign

10:03.036 --> 10:07.106 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
policy background
on their heels.

10:07.106 --> 10:11.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Former front-runner Ben Carson
starting losing support after
one of his advisers told The

10:11.744 --> 10:17.717 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
New York Times that the
neurosurgeon has a weak grasp on
foreign policy. Then today,

10:17.717 --> 10:23.556 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Carson, trying to regain
momentum, released a plan to
protect America. But look at
point

10:23.556 --> 10:29.028 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
number seven: a call to
investigate the Council on
American-Islamic Relations,
known as CAIR,

10:29.028 --> 10:32.866 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
as a -- quote --
"supporter of terrorism."

10:32.866 --> 10:36.636 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The group, a leading advocate
for American Muslims, fired back
in a statement, calling

10:36.636 --> 10:40.640 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Carson's remarks Islamophobia.

10:40.640 --> 10:45.945 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
With Carson struggling, Senators
Ted Cruz and Marco Rubio, more
steeped in security

10:45.945 --> 10:51.851 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
policy, are gaining with
conservatives. One sits on the
Senate's Judiciary and Armed
Services

10:51.851 --> 10:55.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Committees, the other on the
Foreign Relations and
Intelligence panels. Now the two
are turning

10:55.622 --> 10:58.625 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
their fire on each other.

10:58.625 --> 11:02.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Cruz, who's surging in the
polls, has tried to cast Rubio
as authoritarian.

11:02.829 --> 11:08.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEN. TED CRUZ: When it comes to
foreign policy, he wants as much
power in Washington as possible.

11:08.301 --> 11:12.739 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he has agreed with John
McCain, and Lindsey Graham, and,
for that matter, Hillary Clinton

11:12.739 --> 11:16.442 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and Barack Obama, that we should
keep sticking our nose in
foreign entanglements where the

11:16.442 --> 11:21.514 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
results of their policies
has made America less safe.

11:21.514 --> 11:25.051 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Rubio, in turn,
has cast Cruz as bad for the
military.

11:25.051 --> 11:29.389 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEN. MARCO RUBIO: Given the
choice between neo-isolationism
or the defense of our country,

11:29.389 --> 11:34.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he's chosen neo-isolationism,
whether it's weakening our
intelligence-gathering
capabilities,

11:34.093 --> 11:37.397 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or voting against the defense
bills, or voting against for a
budget that substantially
reduces

11:37.397 --> 11:40.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
our defense spending.
Now, these are facts.

11:40.300 --> 11:43.703 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: While they duke
it out, New Jersey Governor
Chris Christie is also on

11:43.703 --> 11:48.241 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the rise, stressing his time
as a federal prosecutor.

11:48.241 --> 11:50.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GOV. CHRIS CHRISTIE (R-NJ),
Presidential Candidate: I was,
you know, in charge of having to
make

11:50.209 --> 11:53.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
many of those decisions in my
office for seven years as U.S.
attorney.

11:53.913 --> 11:58.217 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: The new
security focus, of course, also
sparked Donald Trump's call to

11:58.217 --> 12:02.589 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
block Muslims from entering the
country, and that prompted new
criticism from some of his

12:02.589 --> 12:05.658 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
opponents, like Ohio
Governor John Kasich.

12:05.658 --> 12:08.461 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
GOV. JOHN KASICH (R-OH),
Presidential Candidate: Look,
people don't buy this.

12:08.461 --> 12:11.497 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: And former
Florida Governor Jeb Bush.

12:11.497 --> 12:13.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEB BUSH (R), Presidential
Candidate: There's no evidence
that he's serious about any
policy

12:13.866 --> 12:16.703 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
proposal he's laid out.

12:16.703 --> 12:20.206 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: So far, though,
the national security debate has
seemed to boost, not bruise,

12:20.206 --> 12:22.475 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the Republican front-runner.

12:22.475 --> 12:27.246 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: We have to get
smart. We have to get tough. We
have to be vigilant. We have

12:27.246 --> 12:30.416 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to be vigilant. We
have no choice.

12:30.416 --> 12:35.288 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Meanwhile,
Democrats are trying not to let
Republicans take ownership

12:35.288 --> 12:39.392 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the issue. In Minneapolis
today, Hillary Clinton outlined
her plan for fighting terrorism

12:39.392 --> 12:41.394 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the U.S.

12:41.394 --> 12:45.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON (D),
Presidential Candidate: The
threat we face is daunting, but
America

12:45.465 --> 12:52.438 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has overcome big challenges many
times before. Throughout our
history, we have stared into

12:52.438 --> 12:55.842 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the face of evil and
refused to blink.

12:55.842 --> 12:59.679 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: And, tellingly,
all of the candidates running
for president now stress

12:59.679 --> 13:02.649 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
they're running to be
commander in chief as well.

13:02.649 --> 13:14.327 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Lisa Desjardins.

13:14.327 --> 13:22.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In Baltimore,
residents and officials are
anxiously awaiting a verdict in
the first

13:22.735 --> 13:27.373 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
trial in the death of Freddie
Gray. It has exposed deep cracks
in the city's criminal

13:27.373 --> 13:35.715 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
justice system, race relations
and economic divide. The case
has its roots in the April

13:35.715 --> 13:41.287 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
arrest of 25-year-old Freddie
Gray and his death a week later.

13:41.287 --> 13:45.958 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
After police detained him on a
North Baltimore street, Gray was
handcuffed and loaded into

13:45.958 --> 13:51.531 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a police van. Either then, or
during the subsequent
multiple-stop 45-minute ride, he
suffered

13:51.531 --> 13:53.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
what would become a
fatal spinal injury.

13:53.766 --> 13:55.535 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PROTESTER: Every day, every day!

13:55.535 --> 13:58.471 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PROTESTERS: We will
fight for Freddie Gray!

13:58.471 --> 14:02.742 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Gray's death
galvanized large protests and
neighborhood unrest, despite

14:02.742 --> 14:06.245 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
appeals for calm by his
mother and community leaders.

14:06.245 --> 14:10.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLORIA DARDEN, Mother of Freddie
Gray: I want you all to get
justice for my son, but don't

14:10.149 --> 14:16.656 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do it like this here. Don't tear
up the whole city, man. Just for
him? It's wrong.

14:16.656 --> 14:21.327 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Eventually,
thousands of National Guard
troops were called in to
stabilize the

14:21.327 --> 14:27.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
city and enforce a week-long
curfew. State's attorney Marilyn
Mosby charged six police

14:27.066 --> 14:31.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
officers in May, accusing them
of failing to do anything to
prevent Gray's death.

14:31.738 --> 14:35.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARILYN MOSBY, Baltimore State's
Attorney: At no point was he
secured by a seat belt

14:35.108 --> 14:42.048 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
while in the wagon, contrary to
a BPD general order. Despite Mr.
Gray's seriously deteriorating

14:42.048 --> 14:47.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
medical condition, no medical
assistance was rendered or
summoned for Mr. Gray at that

14:47.920 --> 14:51.057 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
time by any officer.

14:51.057 --> 14:55.027 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Officer William
Porter, the first of the six to
go to court, stands accused

14:55.027 --> 15:00.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of manslaughter, assault,
reckless endangerment and
misconduct.

15:00.600 --> 15:04.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During his two-week trial,
prosecutors blamed him for
failing to buckle Gray into a
seat

15:04.437 --> 15:09.876 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
belt, and for not calling for an
ambulance. They told the jury of
seven women and five

15:09.876 --> 15:16.482 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
men that Porter's inaction
effectively turned the police
van into a casket on wheels.

15:16.482 --> 15:21.554 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In his own defense, Porter said,
when he checked, Gray didn't
seem injured, and his lawyers

15:21.554 --> 15:27.293 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
argued the vehicle's driver, not
Porter, was supposed to ensure
Gray was belted in. Now

15:27.293 --> 15:33.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
police are braced for potential
trouble after a verdict, and the
head of the city's public

15:33.166 --> 15:37.837 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
schools has issued a letter to
the community warning students
that, "Walkouts, vandalism,

15:37.837 --> 15:42.742 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
civil disorder and any form of
violence are not acceptable."

15:42.742 --> 15:48.614 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Right now, the larger issue is
the potential for a mistrial.
This afternoon, jurors sent

15:48.614 --> 15:55.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
out a note saying they are
deadlocked. Judge Barry Williams
ordered them to continue
deliberating.

15:55.588 --> 16:00.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That jury has gone home now
after a second day of
deliberations without reaching a
verdict.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.995 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Juliet Linderman covers
Baltimore for the Associated
Press. She has been at the
trial,

16:02.995 --> 16:05.131 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and she joins me now.

16:05.131 --> 16:10.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Of course, we have to talk first
about this deadlock. What do we
know about it, Juliet?

16:10.102 --> 16:15.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JULIET LINDERMAN, Associated
Press: So, the jury went home
for the day around 5:30, and

16:15.374 --> 16:19.946 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they had been deliberating for
two days. This was the second
day. They had been deliberating

16:19.946 --> 16:24.617 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for about nine hours when they
sent the judge a note saying
that they were deadlocked.

16:24.617 --> 16:30.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's unclear on what charges
they are deadlocked or how many
jurors are disagreeing, but the

16:30.790 --> 16:34.794 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
judge did send them back into
the jury room and said they
should continue deliberations.

16:34.794 --> 16:38.164 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, they will continue
tomorrow morning.

16:38.164 --> 16:43.402 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Has the jury
signaled in any other way, sent
out any other queries about what

16:43.402 --> 16:46.739 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it is that they're curious
about, what -- that they could
reach a deadlock kind of quickly

16:46.739 --> 16:48.574 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
after only two days
of deliberation?

16:48.574 --> 16:51.911 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JULIET LINDERMAN: Sure. Sure.

16:51.911 --> 16:58.050 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Well, they did request
transcripts of William Porter's
testimony that he gave to
investigators

16:58.050 --> 17:03.956 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on April 17. They also wanted
the police transmission tapes.
The judge denied their request
for

17:03.956 --> 17:09.095 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
transcripts, but the jurors will
be able to view those tapes.

17:09.095 --> 17:14.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The jurors have also asked for
clarification on certain terms,
particularly in regards

17:14.967 --> 17:21.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the misconduct in office
charge. They wanted
clarification on, you know, what
an evil motive

17:21.874 --> 17:26.379 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
might mean, so there's a chance
that they are mulling over that
charge, but beyond that

17:26.379 --> 17:28.814 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
would be speculative. We really
don't know what they're doing so
far.

17:28.814 --> 17:32.018 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: What does an evil
motive mean in this legal case?

17:32.018 --> 17:34.620 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JULIET LINDERMAN: Sure.

17:34.620 --> 17:40.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, there are four charges
that William Porter faces. And
that's reckless endangerment,

17:40.393 --> 17:46.432 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which is basically a wanton
disregard for human life, that
William Porter's inaction

17:46.432 --> 17:50.069 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
caused the risk of injury and
death. So the manslaughter
charge stems from Freddie Gray's

17:50.069 --> 17:55.708 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
death and the assault charge
stems from his injuries.

17:55.708 --> 17:58.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Misconduct in office is a little
bit more complicated, because
jurors are going to have

17:58.511 --> 18:06.385 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to determine whether William
Porter acted in a corrupt manner
and whether he, you know,

18:06.385 --> 18:11.991 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
failed in his duty as an
officer, knowingly failed in
that duty. So it's a bit more
complicated,

18:11.991 --> 18:16.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and jurors are probably really
considering that charge very
carefully.

18:16.429 --> 18:20.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And I gather there
has been no lack of drama in the
courtroom, including

18:20.232 --> 18:24.136 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the putting down of a seat belt
on the table to demonstrate to
the jurors.

18:24.136 --> 18:24.603 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JULIET LINDERMAN: Sure.

18:24.603 --> 18:26.272 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Tell me about that.

18:26.272 --> 18:29.508 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JULIET LINDERMAN: Absolutely.

18:29.508 --> 18:34.447 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Prosecutors -- the prosecutor,
Jan Bledsoe, she did dangle the
bloody set belt in front

18:34.447 --> 18:41.287 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of jurors. They say that William
Porter was criminally negligent
when he failed to seat

18:41.287 --> 18:47.126 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
belt Freddie Gray in the back of
the van, and they wanted to
convey to jurors that that

18:47.126 --> 18:51.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was an intentional decision that
he made, and that he ignored
Freddie Gray when he was

18:51.230 --> 18:54.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
asking for medical attention.

18:54.667 --> 18:59.505 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Of course, William Porter told
jurors that he didn't think that
Freddie Gray was injured,

18:59.505 --> 19:02.608 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he was showing no signs of
distress at all, and that he
told his supervisor that

19:02.608 --> 19:06.412 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
he needed to go to the hospital.

19:06.412 --> 19:11.684 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So that's basically how it's
playing out right now. And
jurors are going to have to
decide

19:11.684 --> 19:16.722 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what to believe. William Porter
did take the stand in his own
defense for more than four

19:16.722 --> 19:23.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hours. And during closing
arguments, prosecutors portrayed
William Porter as perhaps not
telling

19:23.796 --> 19:26.332 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the truth. And so jurors are
going to have to decide whether
they believed his testimony.

19:26.332 --> 19:28.801 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Whether he
was credible or not.

19:28.801 --> 19:33.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But remind us. Since there are
six people charged, what exact
role was William Porter?

19:33.005 --> 19:35.207 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He wasn't the driver of the van.

19:35.207 --> 19:39.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JULIET LINDERMAN: He wasn't
the driver of the van.

19:39.145 --> 19:44.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, William Porter basically
responded to a call for help. He
was present at five of

19:44.417 --> 19:49.955 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the six stops that the transport
vehicle carrying Freddie Gray
made on its almost 45-minute

19:49.955 --> 19:53.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
trip from the site of the arrest
at the Gilmor Homes in West
Baltimore to the Western
District

19:53.826 --> 19:58.230 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
police station, where Freddie
Gray arrived unresponsive.

19:58.230 --> 20:04.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Basically, the stop that is
really at the center of this
trial is the van's fourth stop

20:04.403 --> 20:11.844 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at Druid Hill and Dolphin, when
William Porter checked on Gray,
and he picked Gray up from

20:11.844 --> 20:16.449 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the floor of the transport van,
where he was lying on his
stomach with his legs shackled

20:16.449 --> 20:21.120 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and his wrists restrained in
flexi-cuffs, and he put him on a
bench, upright onto a

20:21.120 --> 20:24.523 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
bench.

20:24.523 --> 20:31.397 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And in Porter's words, he told
the van driver, Caesar Goodson,
whose trial is coming up early

20:31.397 --> 20:37.236 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
next year, that Mr. Gray needed
to go to a hospital. But
prosecutors say that Porter

20:37.236 --> 20:40.372 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
should have called for a medic
immediately after Gray indicated
that he was in any sort

20:40.372 --> 20:42.641 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of distress.

20:42.641 --> 20:47.746 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: So, OK, let's talk
about what effect this has had
on the city of Baltimore.

20:47.746 --> 20:52.818 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We know what the immediate
impact was right after -- just
before the charges were brought,

20:52.818 --> 20:57.123 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
right after the charges were
brought. But what kind of --
where is the city tonight,

20:57.123 --> 20:58.090 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
I guess?

20:58.090 --> 21:00.292 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JULIET LINDERMAN: Sure.

21:00.292 --> 21:05.831 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, the city is absolutely
bracing for a verdict. Police --
there is a police presence

21:05.831 --> 21:10.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Baltimore. There was a
presence in Baltimore today.
Police officers from Baltimore
and

21:10.069 --> 21:15.574 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from surrounding jurisdictions
were seen staging around the
city.

21:15.574 --> 21:20.980 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is a crowd of protesters
that had gathered outside of the
courthouse this evening. There

21:20.980 --> 21:25.718 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are demonstrations planned for
whenever the verdict does come
down and also for the following

21:25.718 --> 21:27.853 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
day.

21:27.853 --> 21:33.826 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So I think the city can
absolutely expect
demonstrations. And the police
department

21:33.826 --> 21:38.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is preparing for any sort of
civil unrest that we might see
in the coming days.

21:38.330 --> 21:40.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Are any of the
people who are organizing these
protests are counseling peaceful

21:40.833 --> 21:43.636 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
protests over violent protests?

21:43.636 --> 21:47.306 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JULIET LINDERMAN: Absolutely.

21:47.306 --> 21:54.213 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As we -- you discussed before,
the public school CEO sent a
letter to all families,

21:54.213 --> 21:58.551 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
public school families,
basically saying that civil
disobedience was not going to be
tolerated,

21:58.551 --> 22:04.957 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
that there would be
consequences. And that included
student walkouts.

22:04.957 --> 22:09.195 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There have been peaceful
protests. And students have
played a large role in those
protests.

22:09.195 --> 22:15.834 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In October, students -- students
staged a sit-in, in city hall
that went late into the

22:15.834 --> 22:20.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
night. Some were arrested.
Several students were arrested,
but it was a peaceful
demonstration.

22:20.573 --> 22:25.911 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so the students are urging
for that kind of peaceful civil
disobedience, I think, in

22:25.911 --> 22:31.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the coming days. And the mayor
has also been outspoken, urging
residents to remain peaceful

22:31.050 --> 22:34.420 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as we come into the verdict
whenever it comes down.

22:34.420 --> 22:35.921 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: OK.

22:35.921 --> 22:39.091 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Well, I know that you will be in
the courtroom watching for that.

22:39.091 --> 22:44.363 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Juliet Linderman of the
Associated Press, thank you.

22:44.363 --> 22:50.402 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JULIET LINDERMAN: Thank you.

22:50.402 --> 22:55.641 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Stay with us.

