50:51.248 --> 50:56.720 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was more like, I'm here to be
a student of this for the rest
of my life.

50:56.720 --> 50:59.590 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRANCESCA MAXIME: Cultivating
that lifelong learning is just
what the Poets House co-founders

50:59.590 --> 51:01.759 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
sought.

51:01.759 --> 51:04.428 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Stanley Kunitz, who was twice
poet laureate of the United
States, and arts administrator

51:04.428 --> 51:07.564 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Elizabeth Kray, had a vision.

51:07.564 --> 51:11.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEE BRICCETTI: They felt that
poets were lonely in this
culture and needed a place to
gather,

51:11.001 --> 51:13.570 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to meet, to be nurtured.

51:13.570 --> 51:16.440 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRANCESCA MAXIME: Like other
nonprofits, Poets House requires
public and private financial

51:16.440 --> 51:19.343 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
support to keep its doors open.

51:19.343 --> 51:23.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AZIZA BARNES: A lot of the world
would like to make you believe
that the work you're doing

51:23.414 --> 51:29.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is not important, will not
change anything, particularly
the arts. But I think it's like

51:29.620 --> 51:35.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the only thing that survives
about culture for real. And,
like, people do need it.

51:35.693 --> 51:39.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRANCESCA MAXIME: Including
Cornelius Eady, a poet,
professor, and co-founder of
Cave

51:39.530 --> 51:45.202 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Canem, a national organization
for African-American poets which
rented space from Poets House

51:45.202 --> 51:50.407 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
